Severity: 🔴 Obvious Visual Bug
What's Wrong
Python uses indentation (the spaces at the start of lines) to decide which lines belong inside an if block. If a line is not indented far enough, it runs for everyone — not just when the condition is true.

In your glow-rendering loop, you have:

for body in self.physics.bodies:
