FIX 5 — Model Matrix Transform Order is Wrong
Severity: 🟡 Subtle Visual Bug
What's Wrong
When drawing a 3D sphere, you need to apply several transformations:

S — Scale: resize the unit sphere to the correct visual size
Zt — Tilt: apply the axial tilt (like Earth's 23.5° tilt)
R — Rotate: spin the body on its axis
T — Translate: move it to the correct position in space
These need to happen in the right order. Think of it like getting dressed:

✅ Right order: put on socks, then shoes
❌ Wrong order: put on shoes, then try to put on socks
In 3D graphics with column-major matrices (what pyrr uses), transformations read right to left in the matrix multiplication. So T @ R @ Zt @ S means: first scale, then tilt, then rotate, then translate — which is correct.

Your current code does S @ Zt @ R @ T which means: first translate (move to world position), then rotate, then tilt, then scale in world space. Scaling in world space after translation means the sphere gets stretched relative to the world origin, not relative to itself.

Find It
Search for:

def _model_matrix(self
You will see:

