    def step(self, dt: float):
        if not self.bodies:
            return

        # Divide the total frame time into substeps no larger than MAX_SUBSTEP_S.
        # This keeps the integration stable regardless of speed multiplier.
        # Example: dt = 100 days, MAX_SUBSTEP_S = 1 day → 100 substeps of 1 day each.
        substeps = min(MAX_SUBSTEPS, max(1, math.ceil(dt / MAX_SUBSTEP_S)))
        sub_dt   = dt / substeps

        for _ in range(substeps):
            self._verlet_step(sub_dt)
Why It Works
MAX_SUBSTEP_S is already set to one simulated day (86,400 seconds), which is well-established as a safe integration step for inner-planet orbits. We don't need to measure it dynamically. This removes the entire estimation pass and makes each frame do one-third less work.

