Why the Trails Were "Running Away"
This isn't a separate bug — it was a symptom of Fix 1's problem.

The trail correctly stored body.pos / SCALE (the real physics position). The star sphere was rendering at the wrong, tiny position near the origin. So the trail dots were going to where the star ACTUALLY IS in physics space, while the sphere sat nearly still near the center. It looked like the trail was escaping the star, but actually the star was the thing in the wrong place.

Once Fix 1 is applied, the sphere will move with its trail correctly.
